<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>D3 Tester</title>
  <link href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Montserrat:400,700' rel='stylesheet' type='text/css'>
  <link href='https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/c3/0.4.10/c3.min.css' rel='stylesheet' type='text/css'>
  <script src="http://d3js.org/d3.v3.min.js"></script>
  <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/c3/0.4.10/c3.min.js"></script>
  <%= javascript_include_tag 'application', 'data-turbolinks-track' => true %>
  <script src="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.5/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
  
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag    'application', media: 'all', 'data-turbolinks-track' => true %>
  <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
</head>
<body>
	<header>
		<section>
			<h1 class="logo">D3 Tester</h1>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<h3>Avg. Uptime</h3>
				</li><li class="speed stats" id="now-speed">
					<span>loading...</span>
				</li><li class="speed stats" id="past-speed">
					Prev: <span>loading...</span>
				</li><li class="date">
				</li>
			</ul>
		</section>
	</header>
	<div class="mission-state">
		<p>This Ruby on Rails app was designed as a testing ground for D3.js and libraries that utilize its code base.</p>
	</div>
	<div class="graph-header">
		<p>The bar graphs below represent US Government Spending between 1962 and 2020. The data was scrapped from usgovernmentspending.com using Nokogiri (inside the projects_controller). The projects were: 1) designed with basic D3.js, 2) designed with nvd3.js</p>
	</div>
	<div class="chart"></div>
			<div class="c3-bar-chart"></div>
				<div class="graph-header">
					<p>The Donut charts below were created with nvd3.js and represent: 1) The percentage of NYC libraries by borough, 2) The percentage of square mileage by borough. The data was taken from nyc.gov.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="c3-library-chart col-md-12"></div>
				<div class="c3-land-chart col-md-12"></div>
			</div>
	</div>
	
	
<!-- 	

	Using this object as a starting point helped me to find the variables inside the Nokogiri code.

	<object type="image/svg+xml" data="//b.h-t.co/679f5954-ca03-e511-80c3-0003ff733473">Your browser does not support SVG
	</object>

-->
	<div class='with-3d-shadow with-transitions'>
		
		<div id="graph" class="chartWrap">
    	<svg></svg>
		</div><br>
		<p>When completed, I would like the graph to look more like this: <a href="http://nvd3-community.github.io/nvd3/examples/scatterChart.html">http://nvd3-community.github.io/nvd3/examples/site.html</a></p>
	</div>
</body>
</html>
